I"<p>The Roseberry Gardens estate is one of five estates listed in <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MdX6GlaHDoBdG6CTsvjFaIuPtIa9id5O/view">Sutton’s Local Plan (2018)</a> for potential redevelopment:</p>

<p><img src="/images/suttonplan.png" alt="" /></p>

<p>The estate is also clearly marked in Sutton’s <a href="http://sutton.addresscafe.com/app/exploreit/">Policy Map</a> as a potential renewal area:</p>

<p><img src="/images/suttonpolicymap.png" alt="" /></p>

<p>The estate comprises around a dozen blocks of 2-3 storey maisonettes and around a dozen rows of 2-storey terraced homes. It is located directly adjacent to the <a href="/estates/sutton/benhillestate/">Benhill estate</a> which is a much larger estate, and also earmarked for redevelopment in the local plan.</p>

